---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CompareBody from '../components/CompareBody.astro';
---
<Layout seoSlug="/easy-affiliate-vs-asteris">
  <CompareBody
    rivalName="Easy Affiliate"
    rivalTagline="A WordPress affiliate plugin built by the MemberPress team. Designed to pair with MemberPress-based membership sites."
    rivalUrl="https://easyaffiliate.com"
    intro="Easy Affiliate is built by the MemberPress team and integrates closely with MemberPress for membership-driven affiliate programs. Asteris Affiliates is a standalone self-hosted plugin with WooCommerce, EDD and Surecart adapters in core, two-tier (MLM) referrals from Starter, AI swipe-copy, cloud-assist fraud detection and Stripe Connect direct payouts — included from $149/yr with no MemberPress dependency."
    whenRivalWins={[
      'You already run MemberPress as your membership platform and want first-party affiliate integration',
      'Your entire affiliate program is built around recurring membership-tier commissions',
      'You\'re bundling Easy Affiliate as part of an existing MemberPress purchase and the marginal cost is low for you',
    ]}
    whenAsterisWins={[
      'Standalone — no MemberPress dependency',
      'WooCommerce / EDD / Surecart adapters in core (Easy Affiliate is WC via integration)',
      'AI swipe-copy generator — no Easy Affiliate equivalent',
      'Cloud-assist fraud detection (opt-in, SHA-256 hashed) — no Easy Affiliate equivalent',
      'Stripe Connect Express direct payouts at 0.25%',
      'PayPal API auto-batch payouts',
      'Vanity /go/ landing pages with cookie + view tracking',
      'A/B email testing on transactional emails',
      'Real-time stats REST API (cursor-paginated, transient-cached)',
      'Asteris Starter is $149/yr',
    ]}
    comparisonRows={[
      { feature: 'MemberPress-tight integration', rival: 'Native',               asteris: 'No (standalone)',         win: 'rival' },
      { feature: 'Standalone (no other plugin)',  rival: 'Yes (no hard dep)',    asteris: 'Yes',                      win: 'tie' },
      { feature: 'WooCommerce native',            rival: 'Via integration',      asteris: 'Direct hook-in',           win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'EDD adapter',                   rival: 'Limited',              asteris: 'Included',                 win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'Surecart adapter',              rival: 'Not available',        asteris: 'Included',                 win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'Two-tier (MLM) referrals',      rival: 'Available',            asteris: 'Included from Starter',    win: 'tie' },
      { feature: 'AI swipe-copy generator',       rival: 'Not available',        asteris: 'Included',                 win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'Cloud-assist fraud detection',  rival: 'Not available',        asteris: 'Opt-in (hashed)',          win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'Stripe Connect direct payouts', rival: 'Not available',        asteris: 'Included',                 win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'PayPal API auto-batch',         rival: 'Manual / limited',     asteris: 'Included',                 win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'Vanity /go/ landing pages',     rival: 'Not available',        asteris: 'Included',                 win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'A/B email testing',             rival: 'Not available',        asteris: 'Included',                 win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'WP-CLI commands',               rival: 'Limited',              asteris: 'Full suite',               win: 'asteris' },
      { feature: 'Self-hosted',                   rival: 'Yes',                  asteris: 'Yes',                      win: 'tie' },
      { feature: 'GPL-licensed code',             rival: 'Yes',                  asteris: 'Yes (GPL-2.0+)',           win: 'tie' },
    ]}
  >
    <section class="prose">
      <div class="prose-inner">
        <h2>Easy Affiliate is the MemberPress-bundle pick — Asteris is the standalone pick</h2>
        <p>Easy Affiliate is genuinely the right answer if you already run MemberPress as your membership engine. The integration between the two products is tight, billing-event hooks fire commission credits cleanly, and you're buying from a team you already work with. If MemberPress is your stack, you can probably stop reading this comparison and just pick Easy Affiliate.</p>
        <p>If MemberPress isn't your stack, the picture flips. Easy Affiliate's value proposition is the MemberPress relationship — strip that out and you're paying for a feature surface that lags behind both AffiliateWP and Asteris on every dimension that matters: no AI swipe-copy generator, no cloud-assist fraud detection, no Stripe Connect direct payouts, no Surecart adapter, no A/B email testing. It works, but you're paying for a tool optimised for a stack you don't run.</p>
        <h3>When to switch away from Easy Affiliate</h3>
        <p>The migration trigger we see most often: a store buys Easy Affiliate because it was bundled or cross-promoted with their MemberPress purchase, then realises 6 months in that they wanted standalone affiliate tooling all along. The MemberPress-specific hooks don't add value (you're not using membership tiers as the commission unit), and the standalone feature set is thinner than what's available from dedicated affiliate-first plugins.</p>
        <h3>The cart-coverage gap</h3>
        <p>If you sell anything outside MemberPress — products via WooCommerce, courses via EDD, digital products via Surecart — Asteris's cart adapters in core give you one affiliate ledger across all of it. Easy Affiliate's strength is in MemberPress; its weakness is in everything else. <a href="/features">All Asteris cart integrations →</a></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="prose dark">
      <div class="prose-inner">
        <h2>Migrating from Easy Affiliate</h2>
        <p>Easy Affiliate stores its data in WordPress tables, which makes migration relatively painless. The general migration path: install Asteris alongside Easy Affiliate (they won't conflict), run <code>wp asteris-aff import --source=easyaffiliate</code> to read Easy Affiliate's affiliate + commission tables and recreate matching records in Asteris's tables, verify balances, then switch your tracking to Asteris. See the <a href="/migrate">migration hub</a> for general steps; we'll publish a dedicated Easy Affiliate migration walkthrough as we get more customer migration data from this source.</p>

        <h2>The honest case for staying on Easy Affiliate</h2>
        <p>Stay on Easy Affiliate if MemberPress is the heart of your membership business and you genuinely use the membership-tier commission features. The integration won't be replicated by any standalone plugin — including ours — because we don't have MemberPress-specific hooks. If MemberPress is the centre of your stack, lean into the tight integration. If MemberPress is incidental or unused, <a href="/pricing">Asteris's $149/yr Starter</a> is the lower-friction answer with a larger feature surface and broader cart coverage.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </CompareBody>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose { padding: 64px 24px; background: #fff; border-top: 1px solid var(--c-border); }
  .prose.dark { background: var(--c-bg); }
  .prose-inner { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .prose h2 { font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 32px); margin: 36px 0 18px; }
  .prose h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .prose h3 { font-size: 18px; margin: 24px 0 10px; color: var(--c-mint); }
  .prose p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--c-text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .prose a { color: var(--c-mint); font-weight: 600; }
  .prose code { background: rgba(0,0,0,0.06); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; }
  .prose strong { color: var(--c-text); font-weight: 700; }
</style>
